post_text:
It's official, we're a Google School. In our continued efforts to provide quality education to our students and staff, we have transitioned to Chromebook Laptops and tablets. This ensures that whether in the building or out we have, easy to use, quality computers we can rely on. 🥳 🙂 😁

Acer HP

Es oficial, somos una escuela de Google. En nuestros esfuerzos para una educación de calidad a nuestros estudiantes y personal, hemos mudado a computadoras y tabletas Chromebook. Esto garantiza que, ya sea dentro o fuera del edificio, tengamos computadoras de calidad y fáciles de usar en que podamos confiar.

post_text:
With safety at the forefront of our mind and hearts, we have implemented signage and walking patterns meant to keep us socially distant. When walking in the hallways you will see indicators on the ground informing students know where to safely stand so they are six feet away from others. For the protection of our own staff we are also limiting elevator usage to two people at a time. We’re ensuring the fall 2020 school year is a safe one for all.

Con la seguridad en nuestra mente y corazón, hemos implementado señales y patrones de caminar destinados a mantenernos socialmente distantes. Al caminar por los pasillos, verá indicadores en el suelo que informan a los estudiantes sobre dónde pararse de manera segura para que estén seis pies de distancia a los demás. Para la protección de nuestra personal, también estamos limitando el uso del ascensor a dos personas a la vez. Nos aseguramos de que el año escolar de otoño de 2020 sea seguro para todos.

post_text: Tomorrow morning we will host our third meeting regarding our reopening plan. 8 am in English and 8:40 in Spanish. Please read our plan online before attending. Most of the answers to your questions are on our website. The link goes live five minutes before in your child’s google classroom. Outside emails will be denied access. Only SBCSICA emails can enter the room. Please use your child’s account to enter the meeting. ❤️❤️❤️ Mañana por la mañana organizaremos nuestra tercera reunión sobre nuestro plan de reapertura. 8 am en inglés y 8:40 en español. Lea nuestro plan en línea antes de asistir. La mayoría de las respuestas a sus preguntas se encuentran en nuestro sitio web. El vínculo se publica cinco minutos antes en el aula de Google de su hijo. A los correos electrónicos externos se les negará el acceso. Solo los correos electrónicos de SBCSICA pueden ingresar a la sala. Utilice la cuenta de su hijo para ingresar a la reunión.

post_text:
Monday, May 11th at 4pm Ms. Hey our principal will host an information session for all parents and answer all your questions from the school remote learning survey. Please fill out the remote learning survey and meet Ms. Hey live on Google Meet. The link will go live at 3:55p.m. Please make sure mics are on mute when you enter the room we are expecting a large number of participants. See you all Monday.

***Lunes 11 de mayo a las 4pm Sra. Hey, nuestra directora organizará una sesión de información para todos los padres y responderá todas sus preguntas de la encuesta escolar. Complete la encuesta de aprendizaje remoto y participe con Ms. Hey en Google Meet. El enlace se activará a las 3:55 p.m. Asegúrese de que los micrófonos estén silenciados cuando ingrese a la sala, esperamos esperando muchos participantes. Los veo a todos el lunes.--

post_text:
Can you guess who?.....Our Kindergarten teacher Mrs. Liston!
This is her Caption:
" I never thought I would be a teacher, but teaching found me. It has been such an amazing and rewarding experience to see all of my kiddos grow and learn."

The throwback pictures are as follows:
Me in the yellow shirt is my third grade school pictures

Me in the cap and gown .. that is my kindergarten step up ceremony

The human pyramid is a family tradition with my Dad and his kids that we do for his birthday ... this was the first picture. I was the baby and the smallest so I am all the way at the top.

Me on the ride - This is at Disney on Splash Mountain, I think I was in first grade at the time and as you can see I was terrified!!!!
Thank you Mrs. Liston for all that you do for our students! You are appreciated. #sbcsica #staffappreciation #teachersofinstagram #bronx

post_text:
Evann (5th grade) would like to thank some very important essential workers. 1) Woman with white gown on: my aunt, Yaritza, who is a phlebotomist that is currently transporting COVID19 tests results to and from laboratories in Massachusetts.

2) Man with blue mask: my uncle, David, who is also a phlebotomist and a clinical practice assistant who is also transporting COVID19 testing tubes to and from laboratories in Massachusetts

3) Picture of Police men: the man to the right is my uncle NYPD Police Officer Melendez

4) The young man with the grey hoodie sitting in the grass is my cousin, Joshwin, who is a Residential Behavior Specialist who works with autistic persons in Upstate NY

5) UPS: that is my uncle Tony who works everyday as a UPS delivery driver in NYC.

6) My cousin Edna working as an Immediate Consumption Account Manager providing beverages to Supermarkets and Restaurants throughout NYC.

Thank you to all of them for their dedicated work. #sbcsica #essential #stayhome #thankyou #colorfulbuilding

post_text: Congratulations to our SBCSICA students for receiving a full scholarship to Rosie’s Ballet school two week intensive summer program!Based on their dance, music and theater skills, these four talented students will have the opportunity to work with the best in this rigorous and rewarding program. 🎤🎬🎭Felicitamos a nuestros estudiantes de SBCSICA por recibir una beca completa para el programa de verano intensivo de dos semanas de Rosie's Ballet. Basados en sus habilidades de danza, música y teatro. ¡Estos cuatro estudiantes talentosos tendrán la oportunidad de trabajar con los mejores profesionales del programa!🎤🎭🎬

Échale un 👀a quienes son y esperamos que ellos siguen con su puntualidad! 😎
